         <p style="line-height:24px;letter-spacing:0px; color:#4a4a4a; text-align:justify;list-style-position: inside"><img src="images/arrow.gif"/>  10454 people surveyed; 69% are from rural India while 31% are from urban India</p>
         <p style="line-height:24px;letter-spacing:0px; color:#4a4a4a; text-align:justify;list-style-position: inside"><img src="images/arrow.gif"/>  Overall household spending has increased for 56%, net score down by -3</p>
         <p style="line-height:24px;letter-spacing:0px; color:#4a4a4a; text-align:justify;list-style-position: inside"><img src="images/arrow.gif"/>  Consumption of essentials products increased for 46%, net score at +28</p>
         <p style="line-height:24px;letter-spacing:0px; color:#4a4a4a; text-align:justify;list-style-position: inside"><img src="images/arrow.gif"/>  Consumption of discretionary products increased for 8%, net score reduced to -1</p>
         <p style="line-height:24px;letter-spacing:0px; color:#4a4a4a; text-align:justify;list-style-position: inside"><img src="images/arrow.gif"/>  Consumption of health-related items has increased for 42%, up by 3%</p>
         <p style="line-height:24px;letter-spacing:0px; color:#4a4a4a; text-align:justify;list-style-position: inside"><img src="images/arrow.gif"/>  Media consumption increased for 21%</p>
